\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. C. rubra} (L.) L. C. M. Richard,{\i  Orchid. Eur. Annot.} 38 (1817). Stem 20-60 cm, erect, striate and glandular-pubescent above, with a few brownish, sometimes green-tipped, basal sheaths. Leaves 5-8, 5-12 cm, acute, the lower oblong-lanceolate to lanceolate, the upper linear-lanceolate. Spike up to 12 cm, (2-)3- to 10(-12)-flowered. Flowers bright pink or purplish, open, exceeding most or all of the bracts. Outer perianth-segments 17-22(-25) mm, lanceolate, subacute, patent, glandular-pubescent outside; inner lateral 15-18(-20) mm, ovate-lanceolate, subacute, connivent. Labellum about as long as outer perianth-segments, white, the epichile acute, with purple margin and 7-9 narrow yellowish ridges; spur absent. Ovary glandular-pubescent. 2n = 48.{\i  Woods; usually calcicole. Most of Europe, northwards to S. England and S. Finland.} Al Au Be Br Bu Co Cr Cz Da Fe Ga Ge Gr He †Ho Hs Hu It Ju Lu No Po Rm Rs (B, C, W, K, E) Sa Si Su Tu.
