\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. N. nidus-avis} (L.) L. C. M. Richard,{\i  Orchid. Eur. Annot.} 37 (1817). Stem 20-45 cm, erect; scales 3-5 cm, scarious, sheathing. Racemes 5-21 cm, rather lax below; bracts shorter than ovary, lanceolate-acuminate, scarious; pedicels 3-6 mm, twisted. Perianth-segments 4-6 mm, ovate- to elliptic-oblong, obtuse, yellowish-brown, rarely whitish or yellowish. Labellum 8-12 mm, obliquely pendent, greyish-brown, the undivided part oblong, with 2 small lateral teeth near base, the lobes cordate-oblong, obtuse, divergent. 2n = 36.{\i  Shady woodland, especially on humus-rich soils. Most of Europe, but rare in the extreme north.} All except Az Cr Fa Is Sb.
